🚀 4. First boot optimization (after install)
Login and run:

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
Install core tools immediately:
sudo apt install -y curl wget git vim unzip ca-certificates
Install build essentials (important for Java + Docker builds)
sudo apt install -y build-essential
🔐 5. Enable SSH access (critical for your workflow)

Check SSH:

sudo systemctl status ssh

If needed:

sudo apt install -y openssh-server
🌐 6. Access VM from Windows (best practice)

Find IP:

ip a

Then from Windows:

ssh devops@<VM-IP>

👉 OR use VS Code “Remote SSH” (highly recommended)

🐳 7. DOCKER install (next step after base system)
sudo apt install -y docker.io
sudo usermod -aG docker $USER

Log out and back in.

